Solution: Set App Settings Directly
# Set all Docker registry settings at once for frontend
az webapp config appsettings set `
  --name assetbuilder-frontend `
  --resource-group assetbuilder-rg `
  --settings `
    DOCKER_REGISTRY_SERVER_URL="https://assetbuilderacr.azurecr.io" `
    DOCKER_REGISTRY_SERVER_USERNAME="assetbuilderacr" `
    DOCKER_REGISTRY_SERVER_PASSWORD="D1W3CKAU8KAZWLKADYSMMVE1BMKDBM5IX5R6K4MDYB+ACRAL5UPR"

# Set all Docker registry settings for backend
az webapp config appsettings set `
  --name assetbuilder-backend `
  --resource-group assetbuilder-rg `
  --settings `
    DOCKER_REGISTRY_SERVER_URL="https://assetbuilderacr.azurecr.io" `
    DOCKER_REGISTRY_SERVER_USERNAME="assetbuilderacr" `
    DOCKER_REGISTRY_SERVER_PASSWORD="D1W3CKAU8KAZWLKADYSMMVE1BMKDBM5IX5R6K4MDYB+ACRAL5UPR"
Verify Settings Were Applied
# Check frontend settings
az webapp config appsettings list `
  --name assetbuilder-frontend `
  --resource-group assetbuilder-rg `
  --query "[?name=='DOCKER_REGISTRY_SERVER_PASSWORD'].{name:name, value:value}" `
  --output table

# Check backend settings
az webapp config appsettings list `
  --name assetbuilder-backend `
  --resource-group assetbuilder-rg `
  --query "[?name=='DOCKER_REGISTRY_SERVER_PASSWORD'].{name:name, value:value}" `
  --output table
You should see the password value (not null).
Restart Both Services
az webapp restart --name assetbuilder-backend --resource-group assetbuilder-rg
az webapp restart --name assetbuilder-frontend --resource-group assetbuilder-rg
Wait and Check Logs
# Wait 2 minutes for containers to pull and start
timeout /t 120

# Check frontend logs
az webapp log tail --name assetbuilder-frontend --resource-group assetbuilder-rg
Look for:
✅ Pulling image: assetbuilderacr.azurecr.io/asset-builder-frontend:latest
✅ Container ... for site ... initialized successfully
✅ Container ... started successfully
Alternative: Use Azure Portal